WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:01.199
.

00:01.668 --> 00:04.770
<i> - This is anna.</i>
<i> She's my son's main squeeze.</i>

00:04.805 --> 00:06.438
Do me a favor. Will you get this
young lady a cocktail?

00:06.473 --> 00:08.306
- Actually, I, um--
I have to go.

00:08.341 --> 00:10.208
- What?

00:10.243 --> 00:12.110
Hey, I'm sorry. Look,
I know what you're thinking,

00:12.145 --> 00:13.812
but I told you:
Benny's not me.

00:13.847 --> 00:15.380
- We're wrong for each other,
kelly,

00:15.415 --> 00:18.283
and I think we've been idiots
not to see it.

00:18.318 --> 00:20.352
- He cracked a rib
doing compressions.

00:20.387 --> 00:21.586
- You knew you were supposed
to observe only, correct?

00:21.621 --> 00:23.388
- It was my order, sir.

00:23.423 --> 00:25.090
- You've been ordered
to mandatory retraining.

00:25.125 --> 00:26.592
Next shift.

00:31.264 --> 00:32.497
- Okay, so,
you've done this before.

00:32.532 --> 00:34.132
Are the quizzes open-book,

00:34.167 --> 00:35.634
or should I invest
in flashcards?

00:35.669 --> 00:37.536
- Um, I sort of erased
that experience from my memory.

00:37.571 --> 00:39.471
Disciplinary training is
less like college

00:39.506 --> 00:41.173
and more like traffic school.

00:41.208 --> 00:42.541
- Where are you going?

00:42.576 --> 00:45.177
- Getting a seat.
- In the back?

00:45.212 --> 00:48.413
- Morning, folks.

00:48.448 --> 00:49.614
- These are fine.

00:49.649 --> 00:50.849
- Sorry to drag you all in here

00:50.884 --> 00:53.151
on such a glorious day.

00:53.186 --> 00:55.654
I'm edgar flores, and welcome
to advanced cardiovascular.

00:57.624 --> 01:01.126
Wait. Is this 506 or 507?

01:01.161 --> 01:02.227
- It's 507.

01:02.262 --> 01:04.329
- [sighs] all right. My bad.

01:09.469 --> 01:12.838
- Listen up.
This is ems retraining a.

01:12.873 --> 01:15.874
If you're here, it means
you already screwed up

01:15.909 --> 01:17.576
or pissed someone off once,

01:17.611 --> 01:20.512
so for your own sakes,
you better get wise right now.

01:20.547 --> 01:22.581
There will be no talking,
no texting,

01:22.616 --> 01:24.182
no monkey business
in my classroom.

01:24.217 --> 01:25.517
You break those rules,

01:25.552 --> 01:28.320
and it's back to ias
for the lot of you.

01:28.355 --> 01:30.355
Understood?

01:34.728 --> 01:36.161
- Hi!

01:36.196 --> 01:38.463
- Connie.

01:38.498 --> 01:42.134
Uh, welcome back.
How was the trip?

01:42.169 --> 01:45.104
- It was fine.
- [chuckles]

01:47.240 --> 01:49.508
- um, this is marcy.

01:49.543 --> 01:51.643
She was filling in
while you were out.

01:51.678 --> 01:53.612
Thought it would be good to keep
her around a little bit longer.

01:53.647 --> 01:55.514
You know, many hands
make lighter work.

01:55.549 --> 01:58.350
- Hmm, do they?

02:00.554 --> 02:01.720
- Good luck.

02:07.661 --> 02:09.394
<i> - Hi. It's anna.</i>
<i> Leave me a message</i>

02:09.429 --> 02:11.596
<i> and I'll call you back.</i>
<i> [beep]</i>

02:11.631 --> 02:13.632
- yeah. Hey. It's kelly.

02:13.667 --> 02:17.736
Um, I just want to talk.

02:17.771 --> 02:20.939
Just trying to understand
what happened.

02:20.974 --> 02:23.208
I'm on shift. Call if you can.

02:23.243 --> 02:26.411
- Hey. So,
a few of us were talking

02:26.446 --> 02:28.413
about hitting up the lanes
after shift.

02:28.448 --> 02:30.282
You and anna want to team up?

02:30.317 --> 02:32.284
- She's not returning my calls.

02:32.319 --> 02:34.219
- You serious?
- Mm-hmm.

02:34.254 --> 02:36.288
- What did you do?
- Wish I knew.

02:37.591 --> 02:40.258
[alarm sounding]

02:40.293 --> 02:43.528
<i> - squad 3. Vehicle pin-in.</i>
<i> 1300 west taylor.</i>

02:43.563 --> 02:45.730
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

02:45.765 --> 02:48.734
[siren blaring]

02:50.003 --> 02:52.270
- there it is.

02:52.305 --> 02:54.272
[engine grinding]

02:54.307 --> 02:56.675
- damn it.

02:56.710 --> 02:58.410
- Transmission again?

02:58.445 --> 03:01.380
- Third call in a row
it's been doing this.

03:03.650 --> 03:05.717
- Just forget it.
Just pull over. We'll hoof it.

03:08.622 --> 03:11.690
Cruz, you come with me.
Tony, capp, jaws and tool bag.

03:11.725 --> 03:13.558
- Got it.

03:13.593 --> 03:15.427
[electricity zapping]
- that thing electric?

03:15.462 --> 03:17.529
It looks like the car's
still energized.

03:17.564 --> 03:19.231
- Yeah, we'll approach
from the side.

03:19.266 --> 03:20.699
Those body panels
could be charged.

03:22.802 --> 03:25.437
- Help me! I'm--I'm stuck!

03:25.472 --> 03:27.572
- Just hang in there, okay?
Just gonna make sure it's safe.

03:27.607 --> 03:29.441
We'll get you out.
- Okay.

03:29.476 --> 03:30.775
[electricity zapping]
[flames roar]

03:30.810 --> 03:32.711
- whoa! Lieutenant!
- Hey!

03:32.746 --> 03:34.713
- Aah! Aah!

03:34.748 --> 03:38.650
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:42.822 --> 03:42.888
.

03:43.022 --> 03:45.557
- Hey! Capp, tony, let's move!
- Coming in!

03:45.592 --> 03:48.760
- Please! Please help me!

03:48.795 --> 03:51.563
- How do we cut this guy out
without getting electrocuted?

03:51.598 --> 03:54.499
- We got to break the circuit
from the emergency shut-off.

03:54.534 --> 03:55.667
- Where's that?
- Uh, give me a minute

03:55.702 --> 03:57.535
and I'll tell you.

03:57.570 --> 04:00.538
One wrong cut, body gets
charged, we all get zapped.

04:00.573 --> 04:03.842
- All right, hey, bud,
you sit tight.

04:03.877 --> 04:06.911
- Uh, okay, uh, we got to cut
out the rear quarter panel,

04:06.946 --> 04:09.581
find the main power cable,

04:09.616 --> 04:12.317
and that connects the motor
to the battery.

04:12.352 --> 04:14.586
- How do we know
when we see that?

04:14.621 --> 04:16.721
- Should be orange?
- Beautiful.

04:16.756 --> 04:18.490
All right. Let's go.

04:19.726 --> 04:22.694
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

04:22.729 --> 04:29.701
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:39.012 --> 04:41.680
is that it?

04:41.715 --> 04:43.481
- Yeah. Looks like it.

04:43.516 --> 04:45.417
- All right. Cable cutters.

04:45.452 --> 04:48.920
All right, you guys, stand back
in case this thing pops.

04:48.955 --> 04:54.459
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:54.494 --> 04:55.760
[electricity pops and zaps]

04:55.795 --> 04:58.563
- all right, let's get him
out of there!

04:58.598 --> 04:59.931
- All right, got it.
We're clear.

04:59.966 --> 05:01.833
- Jaws!

05:01.868 --> 05:04.770
[whirring]

05:07.407 --> 05:08.607
- all right.

05:17.517 --> 05:18.817
- Give 'em a hand!

05:20.487 --> 05:23.522
[engine grinding]

05:24.924 --> 05:27.992
- hey, still no good, tony?
- Nothing.

05:28.027 --> 05:30.462
- Squad 3 to main.

05:30.497 --> 05:32.931
We're still on scene here
at 1300 west taylor.

05:32.966 --> 05:35.867
We got a busted transmission.
Requesting assistance.

05:35.902 --> 05:38.970
<i> - Copy that, squad 3. We'll</i>
<i> send a team to your location.</i>

05:39.005 --> 05:40.806
<i> Hang tight.</i>

05:42.041 --> 05:43.875
- Hey, cruz?
Will you do me a favor

05:43.910 --> 05:45.710
and just give me a shout
when the service team gets here?

05:45.745 --> 05:47.579
I'll be back in a minute.
- Yeah, you got it.

05:48.848 --> 05:50.415
- Hey, guys,
I need your help with something.

05:50.450 --> 05:51.983
- Shoot.
- Marcy.

05:52.018 --> 05:54.886
If we don't do something,
connie's gonna eat her alive.

05:54.921 --> 05:56.788
- Ah, the first moment
I met that girl,

05:56.823 --> 05:58.757
I gave her two shifts, tops.

05:58.792 --> 06:00.992
- Exactly. That's why I think--
- oh, hold up. Come on.

06:01.027 --> 06:04.429
Two shifts?
Give her some credit. A month.

06:04.464 --> 06:05.830
- How long she lasts isn't
really what we're talking about.

06:05.865 --> 06:07.766
- A month?
Are you out of your mind?

06:07.801 --> 06:10.535
I know connie.
No way she lasts a week.

06:10.570 --> 06:11.970
- Guys, focus.
- You sure about that?

06:12.005 --> 06:13.805
You want to put your money
where your mouth is?

06:13.840 --> 06:14.939
- Gladly. Ten bucks.

06:14.974 --> 06:18.676
- Twenty.
- Done.

06:18.711 --> 06:21.546
- You know, somehow I feel
like we got off track here.

06:30.790 --> 06:31.923
- Morning.
- Morning.

06:31.958 --> 06:33.758
- Sorry to crash your digs.

06:33.793 --> 06:35.527
Got assigned a temporary
change of quarters

06:35.562 --> 06:36.761
while squad 3's tied up.

06:36.796 --> 06:39.697
- Good to have you.

06:39.732 --> 06:42.000
- Wha--
[both laughing]

06:42.035 --> 06:43.701
- what's up?

06:43.736 --> 06:46.004
- Good to see you, man.
You still floating?

06:46.039 --> 06:48.940
- Nah, pulled a permanent post
here on 6 back in July.

06:48.975 --> 06:50.909
- Had to lock him down
once we realized

06:50.944 --> 06:53.077
how much he sucks at hold 'em.
[all chuckle]

06:53.112 --> 06:55.780
- guys, jason kannell. Came up
in the same neighborhood.

06:55.815 --> 06:58.516
- Oh, I bet you got
some stories, huh?

06:58.551 --> 07:00.852
- Ooh. Sworn to secrecy.

07:00.887 --> 07:03.888
But I'll tell you this:
Matt was my inspiration

07:03.923 --> 07:05.590
for joining the cfd.
- Nah.

07:05.625 --> 07:06.891
- Seriously?
- Once he snuck through

07:06.926 --> 07:08.893
the academy,
I knew I needed to apply.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.829
Had to be around to clean up
whatever mess he makes.

07:10.864 --> 07:12.130
Am I right?

07:12.165 --> 07:14.900
- Much appreciated.
[all laugh]

07:20.840 --> 07:22.707
- help you with something?

07:22.742 --> 07:24.742
- Yeah. I'm looking
for anna turner.

07:24.777 --> 07:27.045
I'm a friend.
- Oh, she's not in.

07:27.080 --> 07:28.646
- Do you know
when she'll be back?

07:28.681 --> 07:30.148
- She took leave yesterday.

07:30.183 --> 07:33.518
- Leave? For how long?

07:33.553 --> 07:36.154
- Didn't say.

07:36.189 --> 07:38.890
- Did she say why?
- Mm-mm.

07:43.630 --> 07:46.130
But if you see her,
can you do me a favor?

07:46.165 --> 07:47.833
- Sure.

07:49.068 --> 07:51.069
- Becca's been asking about her.

07:51.104 --> 07:53.638
They usually start the day off
with a story.

07:53.673 --> 07:56.107
Do you mind letting her know
that she says hi?

07:56.142 --> 07:58.844
- Yeah. Will do. Thanks.

08:04.684 --> 08:06.684
- When we hand over
our trauma victim,

08:06.719 --> 08:09.854
we're gonna keep in our mind
the mist protocol.

08:09.889 --> 08:14.626
We're gonna describe
the mechanism of the injury,

08:14.661 --> 08:17.095
the extent of the injury itself,

08:17.130 --> 08:19.764
report the vital signs
of the injury,

08:19.799 --> 08:21.032
and after that...

08:21.067 --> 08:22.868
Anyone?

08:24.871 --> 08:27.171
Gabriela dawson?

08:27.206 --> 08:30.174
- Sorry?
- The t in the mist protocol.

08:30.209 --> 08:32.110
What does it stand for?

08:32.145 --> 08:34.178
- Uhh...

08:34.213 --> 08:37.649
Take 'em to the hospital?

08:37.684 --> 08:39.851
- Is that a joke?
- No. It's just

08:39.886 --> 08:42.120
we do 20 hand-offs a shift.

08:42.155 --> 08:43.988
I mean, at this point,
we have a mind-meld

08:44.023 --> 08:45.657
with the hospital intake staff.

08:45.692 --> 08:47.726
There's no time for word games.

08:50.863 --> 08:53.231
- You can put your hand
down now.

08:53.266 --> 08:56.634
The t stands
for treatments administered.

08:56.669 --> 08:58.236
- Ahh.

09:00.239 --> 09:04.709
- Turn to page 232. Sepsis.

09:04.744 --> 09:07.145
- Psst. Psst. Hey, marcy.
Marcy, hey.

09:07.180 --> 09:08.846
- Hey. Are you okay?

09:08.881 --> 09:10.648
- I'm great.
I just wanted to swing by

09:10.683 --> 09:12.850
and just pass along
a few pro tips

09:12.885 --> 09:15.186
when it comes to dealing
with connie.

09:15.221 --> 09:17.655
- I don't follow.

09:17.690 --> 09:20.058
- How do I put this?
There are ground rules, okay?

09:20.093 --> 09:22.026
You don't ask questions,
you know?

09:22.061 --> 09:23.995
You avoid making eye contact.

09:24.030 --> 09:25.930
She may perceive that
as a challenge.

09:25.965 --> 09:27.765
- Brian, super sweet,

09:27.800 --> 09:30.201
but I think you're overreacting
just a tad.

09:30.236 --> 09:34.072
- I--it's not an overreaction.
You just don't know her.

09:36.075 --> 09:38.009
- Is it too late to get in
on the betting?

09:38.044 --> 09:39.210
- Oh, no.
- Okay. Okay.

09:39.245 --> 09:41.012
[alarm sounding]

09:41.047 --> 09:43.848
<i> - truck 81. Ambo 97.</i>
<i> Trapped person.</i>

09:43.883 --> 09:45.249
<i> Corner of bosworth</i>
<i> and greenview.</i>

09:45.284 --> 09:48.687
[siren blaring]

09:53.793 --> 09:55.259
- what have we got?

09:55.294 --> 09:57.996
- Tenant refusing to comply
with an eviction notice.

10:00.733 --> 10:03.067
- Dude's a nutball. He's been
given multiple warnings

10:03.102 --> 10:04.902
the past few weeks.

10:04.937 --> 10:07.772
Every time I broach the subject,
he becomes erratic.

10:07.807 --> 10:09.073
Should've called you people
sooner.

10:09.108 --> 10:10.875
- Not sure how we're supposed
to help.

10:10.910 --> 10:12.110
- Oh, you'll see.

10:13.980 --> 10:16.047
- Marvin.
- Go away!

10:16.082 --> 10:17.782
- Marvin,
you have some visitors here.

10:17.817 --> 10:19.851
- Get out! I need to be here!

10:23.789 --> 10:23.888
.

10:23.989 --> 10:26.724
- Marvin, want to tell me
what happened?

10:26.759 --> 10:28.059
- I have to be here.
I made a promise.

10:28.094 --> 10:30.028
- You're not looking so hot.

10:30.063 --> 10:32.697
- Crush syndrome.
The concrete's expanding,

10:32.732 --> 10:34.399
restricting blood flow.

10:34.434 --> 10:36.234
We got to get fluids
in this guy fast.

10:36.269 --> 10:38.169
- Otis, we need the chisels.
<i> - Copy that.</i>

10:38.204 --> 10:40.138
- Marvin, we're
with the fire department.

10:40.173 --> 10:42.040
The concrete you're in is
killing you.

10:42.075 --> 10:43.875
We have to get you out.
- Get the hell away from me!

10:43.910 --> 10:45.176
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

10:45.211 --> 10:46.778
- Marvin, listen.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.312
There's saline and bi-carb
in this, okay?

10:48.347 --> 10:50.181
It's gonna save your life.

10:50.216 --> 10:52.450
- No, no, no.
- Hey, marvin. Look at me.

10:52.485 --> 10:56.721
Whoever you made that promise
to, I'm sure they'll understand.

10:56.756 --> 10:58.322
- They don't think like us.

10:58.357 --> 11:00.792
They're from another place.

11:00.827 --> 11:02.760
I know you think I'm stupid,
but I'm not.

11:02.795 --> 11:04.429
I know what I know!
- No, no, no.

11:04.464 --> 11:06.665
- Casey,
he's running out of time.

11:09.135 --> 11:10.435
- You're here.

11:16.743 --> 11:19.110
- Otis, keep the light on.

11:22.215 --> 11:24.115
Guys?

11:27.253 --> 11:30.755
Marvin, hey.

11:30.790 --> 11:33.491
Listen. Don't tell anyone.

11:33.526 --> 11:37.462
We had to come in disguise.
Okay?

11:37.497 --> 11:40.732
Yeah. We're gonna get you
out of here,

11:40.767 --> 11:43.167
take you someplace safe, okay?

11:43.202 --> 11:45.903
- Yes. Thank you.

11:45.938 --> 11:48.272
I got pins and needles all over.

11:48.307 --> 11:50.842
- That's part of the plan.
But you did great.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.410
Didn't he, guys?

11:52.445 --> 11:54.746
- Yeah. Uh-huh.
- Yeah. Good. Oh, yeah.

11:54.781 --> 11:57.148
- You did a great job, marvin.

11:57.183 --> 11:59.217
- Ah--
- all right? You're good.

11:59.252 --> 12:01.286
- Take a deep breath.
- Here.

12:03.322 --> 12:05.123
- We're good.

12:05.158 --> 12:08.126
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

12:08.161 --> 12:10.228
- [whimpers]
- look at me. All right?

12:10.263 --> 12:11.529
Stay with me. Just keep
your eyes on the light.

12:11.564 --> 12:13.331
- Okay. Okay.
- Okay?

12:13.366 --> 12:14.432
- There's gonna be
a little noise, marvin.

12:14.467 --> 12:15.833
- There we go.

12:15.868 --> 12:17.869
- Ready?
Here we go.

12:17.904 --> 12:19.403
[buzzing]

12:19.438 --> 12:21.939
- [whimpering]
- it's okay. It's okay.

12:21.974 --> 12:24.175
Just breathe. Just breathe.

12:24.210 --> 12:25.510
[buzzing]

12:25.545 --> 12:27.779
- [whimpering]

12:43.262 --> 12:44.863
- you're okay.

12:48.467 --> 12:49.967
- Lift him up.

12:50.002 --> 12:52.203
- You got it?
- [grunts]

12:54.841 --> 12:57.508
- he's lost consciousness.

12:57.543 --> 12:58.943
Ah--hey.

13:01.380 --> 13:02.914
Lost his pulse.

13:04.951 --> 13:06.584
Come on.

13:06.619 --> 13:10.855
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:10.890 --> 13:12.423
come on!

13:12.458 --> 13:15.026
- [gasps]
- there we go.

13:15.061 --> 13:17.562
- Main, this is 81.
Victim is breathing, conscious,

13:17.597 --> 13:19.297
waiting for paramedics.

13:19.332 --> 13:20.998
Nice job.

13:21.033 --> 13:22.967
- Don't mention it.

13:30.943 --> 13:33.611
- [chuckling]
heard you caught a live one.

13:33.646 --> 13:35.413
- See the kind of fun we have?

13:35.448 --> 13:37.215
You should come hang with us
more often.

13:37.250 --> 13:39.250
- Might want to vacate
that seat.

13:39.285 --> 13:41.052
Wars have been started
over less.

13:41.087 --> 13:42.854
- Noted.

13:46.092 --> 13:48.626
- Kelly severide,
jason kannell, squad 6.

13:48.661 --> 13:51.495
- Nice to meet you.
- Heard a lot of good things.

13:51.530 --> 13:53.364
- Yeah, sure thing.
Will you excuse me?

13:53.399 --> 13:54.966
- Yeah, of course.

13:58.604 --> 14:00.938
Guess I should tell the guys
it's time to get out of here.

14:00.973 --> 14:02.473
- Glad we could have a minute,
at least.

14:02.508 --> 14:03.975
- Yeah, absolutely.

14:04.010 --> 14:05.877
Hey, drink tomorrow
at molly's at noon?

14:05.912 --> 14:08.546
- You're buying.
- All right.

14:08.581 --> 14:10.314
- Hey.

14:10.349 --> 14:12.016
- Hey.

14:12.051 --> 14:14.518
- Are you all right?
You got that look on your face.

14:14.553 --> 14:16.921
- Yeah, I'm good.
- Right.

14:16.956 --> 14:19.957
Kelly, hey.

14:19.992 --> 14:22.526
What happened?

14:22.561 --> 14:25.363
- I just stopped in
to pediatrics at chicago med,

14:25.398 --> 14:27.598
and apparently anna took leave.

14:27.633 --> 14:29.433
No warning. She just left.

14:29.468 --> 14:33.304
- What? Okay, how bad
was this fight you had?

14:33.339 --> 14:34.572
- It wasn't even a fight.

14:36.943 --> 14:39.610
- Okay. There's--
there's no way--

14:39.645 --> 14:44.048
there's no way she up and leaves
you and her career

14:44.083 --> 14:46.550
just like that.

14:46.585 --> 14:48.586
No. Something's up.

14:53.526 --> 14:55.993
<i> [somber music]</i>

14:56.028 --> 15:02.934
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:21.754 --> 15:23.521
- it's been real.

15:26.692 --> 15:28.092
- Time's up.

15:28.127 --> 15:29.327
- Oh, shoot. Wait.

15:29.362 --> 15:31.729
- No waiting. Pencils down.

15:31.764 --> 15:33.498
Pencils down!

15:35.634 --> 15:38.102
- Um, what does it take to pass?

15:38.137 --> 15:39.737
- 75.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.505
- And if we don't?

15:41.540 --> 15:44.442
- We're gonna get to know
each other real well.

15:50.549 --> 15:53.517
[chatter and music playing]

15:53.552 --> 15:55.987
- hey, hey!

15:56.022 --> 15:58.356
- Haven't been here
since the early days.

15:58.391 --> 16:01.625
I dig what they've done
to the place.

16:01.660 --> 16:05.129
- So, how's life in squad 6?
What's the vibe over there?

16:05.164 --> 16:07.098
- Oh, crew is tight.
- Yeah?

16:07.133 --> 16:10.167
- Real tight.
Sunday dinners every week.

16:10.202 --> 16:12.536
We all know
each other's business.

16:12.571 --> 16:15.406
Hell, we're like family.

16:15.441 --> 16:18.409
Still get guff for being
the only single guy, though.

16:18.444 --> 16:20.445
- That'll never stop.

16:21.781 --> 16:24.548
- I hear you finally
tied the knot.

16:24.583 --> 16:26.684
- Eh? Eh?

16:26.719 --> 16:29.387
- Matt casey!

16:29.422 --> 16:31.455
Respectable guy.

16:31.490 --> 16:35.126
Officer on the cfd,
happily married,

16:35.161 --> 16:37.595
and a damned alderman to boot.

16:37.630 --> 16:39.663
- Can't be entirely respectable.

16:39.698 --> 16:42.700
- I'm just saying.

16:42.735 --> 16:45.636
You done good, brother.

16:45.671 --> 16:48.506
Considering the homes
you and I came up in?

16:48.541 --> 16:50.575
It wasn't necessarily
in the cards.

17:01.153 --> 17:04.155
- Um, I--I just need

17:04.190 --> 17:05.623
five minutes
with your daughter, anna.

17:05.658 --> 17:08.225
That's it.

17:08.260 --> 17:12.063
- Ah, she's out.

17:12.098 --> 17:13.631
- Please?

17:13.666 --> 17:15.232
I know what's going on.

17:15.267 --> 17:17.101
- [sighs] dad, it's okay.

17:22.808 --> 17:26.544
What do you want, kelly?

17:26.579 --> 17:28.613
- What's the prognosis?

17:32.218 --> 17:36.220
- My t-cell count is elevated.

17:36.255 --> 17:39.090
It's off the charts.

17:39.125 --> 17:42.627
The cancer's in my bones.
It's, like, everywhere.

17:44.830 --> 17:48.199
The time frame's really hard
to predict, but...

17:48.234 --> 17:51.202
Doctors are talking management

17:51.237 --> 17:54.205
rather than treatment, so...

17:54.240 --> 17:56.107
It's gonna win.

17:58.844 --> 18:00.811
- You can fight.
- Stop selling me this fairytale

18:00.846 --> 18:02.513
about how things are gonna be
if I just fight.

18:02.548 --> 18:03.781
Not while I'm doing
everything I can...

18:03.816 --> 18:05.149
- Anna.
- To wrap my mind around

18:05.184 --> 18:07.251
what's real.

18:07.286 --> 18:10.855
- Anna--
- kelly, I can't, like--

18:10.890 --> 18:12.890
[crying]
I can't do this with you.

18:12.925 --> 18:14.558
You have to go.
- I'm not--

18:14.593 --> 18:16.127
- I'm sorry.
- If you let me--

18:16.162 --> 18:18.162
- you have to go.
- I--

18:18.197 --> 18:25.236
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:32.277 --> 18:32.343
.

18:32.444 --> 18:34.879
- Lieutenant?
There's someone looking for you.

18:39.852 --> 18:42.286
- Hey.
- Hey, lieutenant.

18:42.321 --> 18:43.854
- Um--
- I'll be quick.

18:43.889 --> 18:45.623
Sorry to barge in on you here
at work like this.

18:45.658 --> 18:47.591
- No, no, no.
You're not barging in.

18:47.626 --> 18:52.830
- Anna--she has been so strong.

18:52.865 --> 18:54.431
So much stronger
than even I've been able

18:54.466 --> 18:58.302
to muster through much of it,
but, uh...

18:58.337 --> 19:01.606
Just because she's strong
doesn't mean she's right.

19:06.212 --> 19:07.578
- Do want a seat?

19:07.613 --> 19:09.347
- Do you mind?

19:15.254 --> 19:18.422
Anna...[sighs]

19:18.457 --> 19:20.891
she was at her best when
the two of you were together.

19:20.926 --> 19:25.596
You gave her something.
You made her smile again.

19:25.631 --> 19:30.434
And this latest turn caught her
off-guard.

19:30.469 --> 19:33.504
And she is doing her best
to handle it.

19:34.540 --> 19:38.309
Whether or not she knows it,

19:38.344 --> 19:41.279
she needs you to be there.

19:43.949 --> 19:46.884
Please,

19:46.919 --> 19:49.287
don't give up on her.

19:52.524 --> 19:54.225
- What did you put down
on the question

19:54.260 --> 19:56.393
about atypical seizures?

19:56.428 --> 19:59.496
- Which one was that?
- Uh, where we had to identify

19:59.531 --> 20:03.234
the type of seizure
based on symptoms.

20:03.269 --> 20:05.536
- Uh, you know what, brett?
I just winged it.

20:05.571 --> 20:08.239
[phones chime and buzz]

20:09.408 --> 20:13.277
- oh, that was fast.
Results are in.

20:13.312 --> 20:15.646
Ha! 98!

20:15.681 --> 20:19.016
Oh, see, dawson, you put a
little time and effort into it,

20:19.051 --> 20:20.684
it really pays off.

20:20.719 --> 20:24.388
- That's--that's awesome.
Congrats. Truly.

20:24.423 --> 20:26.991
That's great.

20:27.026 --> 20:28.459
What?

20:28.494 --> 20:30.428
- Tell me.
Did you pass?

20:31.597 --> 20:33.564
Oh, no, dawson.
Look, it's okay,

20:33.599 --> 20:36.567
because I'm gonna be a really
good tutor, and next time--

20:44.777 --> 20:48.512
- casey, I want you to take 81
to the shops.

20:48.547 --> 20:50.981
After what happened to squad,
we finally got a budget approval

20:51.016 --> 20:52.383
for more frequent
service checks.

20:52.418 --> 20:55.552
- You got it, chief.

20:55.587 --> 20:57.955
- Connie!

20:57.990 --> 20:59.423
- Sweet mother of god.

20:59.458 --> 21:01.325
- Oh, I should've put money
on this.

21:01.360 --> 21:03.694
- Hi. I made you something.
It's just a little home remedy.

21:03.729 --> 21:06.063
I have ginger to help
with your immune system,

21:06.098 --> 21:07.564
turmeric to help with the blood,

21:07.599 --> 21:09.433
and burdock
just 'cause it's tasty.

21:09.468 --> 21:11.702
- You haven't put any of that
in the eggs, have you?

21:11.737 --> 21:14.405
See, I'm very sensitive
to extreme flavors.

21:14.440 --> 21:17.341
- No. Don't worry.

21:17.376 --> 21:18.809
- I am not drinking that.

21:18.844 --> 21:21.078
- Oh, bup-bup-bup.
That's the cranky cold talking,

21:21.113 --> 21:22.713
and I will not have it.

21:22.748 --> 21:24.715
Tell you what. I am going
to put this on your desk

21:24.750 --> 21:28.052
right next to the zinc lozenges,
and you'll thank me in an hour.

21:28.087 --> 21:29.687
- Heh-heh.

21:29.722 --> 21:33.057
- Hey, guys,
let's pack breakfast to go.

21:33.092 --> 21:35.426
Got to get to the shops.
Chief's orders.

21:39.365 --> 21:41.332
<i> - So, here's a question:</i>

21:41.367 --> 21:43.600
If marcy doesn't make it
to sundown,

21:43.635 --> 21:46.603
does that technically count
as one shift, or two?

21:46.638 --> 21:48.772
- One.
- Two. Two!

21:48.807 --> 21:52.042
- Hey, hey, hey, that's a human
being you're talking about.

21:52.077 --> 21:53.377
Doesn't she
at least deserve to--

21:53.412 --> 21:54.745
- lieutenant, what's your take?

21:54.780 --> 21:56.447
- She makes it to lunch,
it's two.

21:56.482 --> 21:59.450
If not, it's one.
- Baloney!

21:59.485 --> 22:01.118
- I'd say that's fair.
- Ha!

22:01.153 --> 22:03.420
- No.
<i>- Squad 6 requesting assistance</i>

22:03.455 --> 22:05.823
<i> on that construction accident</i>
<i> at cermak and troy.</i>

22:05.858 --> 22:07.691
<i> Truck 63, do you copy?</i>

22:07.726 --> 22:09.426
- Hey, we're
right around the corner,

22:09.461 --> 22:11.395
you want to pick that up.
<i> - Copy that.</i>

22:11.430 --> 22:13.497
- Truck 81 to main.
We're about two blocks

22:13.532 --> 22:15.032
from squad 6's incident.

22:15.067 --> 22:16.500
Happy to take it in.

22:16.535 --> 22:18.102
<i> - Take it in, truck 81.</i>

22:18.137 --> 22:20.371
<i> Return to quarters, 63.</i>
<i> - All right.</i>

22:20.406 --> 22:22.373
<i> - Copy that.</i>
<i>Truck 63 returning to quarters.</i>

22:22.408 --> 22:23.741
- Truck 81 on route.

22:23.776 --> 22:25.776
[siren blares]

22:25.811 --> 22:27.778
- let's get to work.

22:27.813 --> 22:31.115
[siren blaring]

22:32.684 --> 22:34.618
- truck 81 is on the scene.

22:34.653 --> 22:36.721
<i> - Copy that, 81.</i>

22:41.760 --> 22:43.894
- Get masks ready just in case
they need some help.

22:51.570 --> 22:52.870
<i> - The victim...</i>
<i> [radio static]</i>

22:52.905 --> 22:54.671
- repeat that, squad 6.

22:54.706 --> 22:56.707
<i> - [distorted yelling,</i>
<i> radio static]</i>

22:56.742 --> 22:58.809
- squad 6, repeat.

22:58.844 --> 23:00.177
<i> - [distorted]</i>
<i> damn it, I said--</i>

23:00.212 --> 23:02.446
[explosion]

23:04.850 --> 23:07.551
<i> - mayday! Mayday!</i>
<i> Firefighter down!</i>

23:07.586 --> 23:11.722
<i> Firefighter down!</i>
<i> - Doyle! Kannell! Report!</i>

23:11.757 --> 23:13.624
- Get a reading on that gas.

23:13.659 --> 23:16.627
- Truck 81 to main.
We've got a mayday emergency.

23:16.662 --> 23:18.662
Gas explosion.
Firefighters down.

23:18.697 --> 23:20.497
I need an ems plan one.

23:20.532 --> 23:21.632
Give me some rope bags.
I'm going in.

23:21.667 --> 23:23.534
- No way. Not alone.

23:23.569 --> 23:25.869
- I'm not risking any more
lives! That's an order!

23:25.904 --> 23:27.638
<i> - Ems plan one en route.</i>

23:29.608 --> 23:32.209
- Doyle! Kannell!

23:32.244 --> 23:35.212
- Ignition burned the gas away,
but lel levels are climbing.

23:35.247 --> 23:36.814
Something down there is
still leaking.

23:36.849 --> 23:38.949
- What's my window?
- Few minutes, tops.

23:38.984 --> 23:41.218
- Be ready for me then.
And anyone who doesn't have

23:41.253 --> 23:42.920
to be here, keep back.

23:44.523 --> 23:47.491
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

23:47.526 --> 23:51.796
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:56.301 --> 23:56.767
.

23:56.934 --> 23:59.670
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

23:59.705 --> 24:04.174
- squad 6! Doyle! Kannell!
Call out!

24:04.209 --> 24:06.009
Call out!

24:06.044 --> 24:11.782
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:11.817 --> 24:14.819
[sirens blaring]

24:15.954 --> 24:17.488
- all right, come on, guys.

24:17.523 --> 24:19.122
Let's get these ropes
standing by.

24:19.157 --> 24:21.124
- Lower explosive limits are
still on the rise.

24:21.159 --> 24:22.993
We're at 50% limit.

24:23.028 --> 24:25.762
52%. Still climbing.

24:25.797 --> 24:28.799
- Okay. Casey!

24:28.834 --> 24:30.067
How we doing?

24:30.102 --> 24:32.837
- Squad 6! Call out!

24:37.976 --> 24:40.845
Squad 6! Call out!

24:44.783 --> 24:47.784
- I need help!

24:47.819 --> 24:49.987
- Who's there?

24:50.022 --> 24:52.756
- I need help!

24:52.791 --> 24:58.962
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:58.997 --> 25:01.231
- here!

25:01.266 --> 25:03.166
Here we go.
- [grunting]

25:03.201 --> 25:05.135
- it's doyle.
- Got him.

25:05.170 --> 25:07.805
Hey! Kannell! Come back here.

25:09.875 --> 25:13.077
Kannell! Kannell!

25:14.212 --> 25:19.850
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:19.885 --> 25:23.921
- casey!
How we doing?

25:23.956 --> 25:25.890
- I need those ropes!

25:38.837 --> 25:40.337
- Here.
- All right.

25:40.372 --> 25:42.205
- He's been secured.
Take him up.

25:42.240 --> 25:44.041
- Up on rope.

25:47.913 --> 25:50.948
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:50.983 --> 25:52.783
- we got him.

25:57.189 --> 25:59.756
- All right.

25:59.791 --> 26:01.191
- Watch that meter.

26:01.226 --> 26:05.195
Those limits rise above 70%,
you clear out!

26:05.230 --> 26:06.930
- Where are you going?

26:06.965 --> 26:08.365
Hey! Casey!

26:08.400 --> 26:15.806
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:23.949 --> 26:26.350
- hey! Hey.

26:26.385 --> 26:28.185
Come on.

26:28.220 --> 26:30.053
- I could only grab farage.

26:30.088 --> 26:32.222
- Whoa. Wait.
- I've got to get coleman!

26:32.257 --> 26:36.226
- Whoa! Hey! We can't go back
until we ventilate.

26:36.261 --> 26:38.161
- I'm going back!
- Come on!

26:38.196 --> 26:40.230
- Limit's at 60%.

26:41.833 --> 26:43.867
[beeping]

26:43.902 --> 26:45.168
65.

26:45.203 --> 26:47.004
- This is bad.

26:47.039 --> 26:50.040
- I'm going back.
Come on. Come on!

26:50.075 --> 26:52.242
Let's go! Let's go!

26:57.315 --> 27:00.417
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:00.452 --> 27:02.853
[meter beeping]

27:07.926 --> 27:10.628
- here they come. All right,
let's go. Get the lines in.

27:17.102 --> 27:18.835
- Casey, we're at 70%.

27:18.870 --> 27:21.105
- All right, take him up.
- Up on rope.

27:28.246 --> 27:30.247
- Got him!
- Got him!

27:30.282 --> 27:33.283
[both breathing heavily]

27:37.222 --> 27:38.922
[indistinct]

27:41.727 --> 27:43.927
- kannell, we need the rope.

27:47.165 --> 27:49.332
Bring the board in.

27:49.367 --> 27:53.036
Herrmann,
get this tunnel ventilated.

27:53.071 --> 27:54.304
We have to send someone
down there

27:54.339 --> 27:55.906
to get coleman and the worker.

27:55.941 --> 27:56.974
- Copy.

27:58.343 --> 28:01.378
Let's get that ventilation
in there right now!

28:09.254 --> 28:16.293
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:19.765 --> 28:21.999
- his airway's compromised.
We need to intubate.

28:26.938 --> 28:28.271
- Looks like he's got
epiglottitis.

28:28.306 --> 28:30.741
Grab me a straight blade
and a 6 1/2 et tube.

28:52.564 --> 28:54.264
-Got him.

28:58.570 --> 29:00.270
- [sighs]

29:08.980 --> 29:11.114
- doyle?
- No.

29:11.149 --> 29:13.950
- Three dead, one critical.

29:13.985 --> 29:15.753
- It's a damn nightmare.

29:20.392 --> 29:24.228
- God help that kid.
I can't imagine.

29:31.837 --> 29:33.537
- Casey.

29:35.407 --> 29:37.207
- What happened?

29:37.242 --> 29:40.110
- Squad 6 responded to a call.

29:40.145 --> 29:43.380
Partial collapse,
construction worker trapped.

29:43.415 --> 29:46.316
Turns out there were high levels
of combustible gas.

29:46.351 --> 29:49.352
Rescue tools threw a spark,

29:49.387 --> 29:52.189
coleman and the worker were
killed instantly.

29:52.224 --> 29:54.124
Kannell ducked down
a side tunnel.

29:54.159 --> 29:57.227
We just lost doyle.
Farage appears to be hanging on,

29:57.262 --> 29:59.462
but...[sighs]

29:59.497 --> 30:01.565
kannell was the only one
to walk away.

30:08.106 --> 30:09.306
- How the hell
did they get so deep

30:09.341 --> 30:11.275
without taking
a proper gas reading?

30:14.479 --> 30:18.381
I don't want to see a single
detail missing in your report.

30:18.416 --> 30:19.583
Understood?

30:19.618 --> 30:21.451
- Yes, chief.

30:26.892 --> 30:29.860
<i> [somber music]</i>

30:29.895 --> 30:37.067
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:47.078 --> 30:48.278
- so, what's the latest?

30:48.313 --> 30:50.180
- Farage is on a ventilator.

30:50.215 --> 30:52.582
Respiratory burns,
shattered bones.

30:52.617 --> 30:55.151
Surgery's scheduled
for tomorrow morning.

30:55.186 --> 30:57.554
- It's a miracle that he
survived that blast at all.

30:57.589 --> 31:00.557
- According to kannell, doyle
covered him when the blast hit,

31:00.592 --> 31:04.394
saved farage's life.

31:04.429 --> 31:07.130
- That's a hell of a burden
to be walking around with.

31:10.168 --> 31:13.436
- We'll have a fundraiser
at molly's tomorrow night.

31:13.471 --> 31:15.305
Let's take care of the families.

31:15.340 --> 31:17.507
- Absolutely.

31:19.577 --> 31:22.512
- Sorry,
visiting hours are over.

31:22.547 --> 31:24.447
Family can stay,

31:24.482 --> 31:26.549
but everyone else needs
to come back in the morning.

31:26.584 --> 31:28.252
- Understood.

31:29.421 --> 31:31.154
Come on, guys.

31:32.524 --> 31:39.429
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:02.320 --> 32:03.954
- hi.

32:03.989 --> 32:05.221
Anna's friend, right?

32:05.256 --> 32:06.957
- Yeah.

32:06.992 --> 32:10.193
Listen, I was wondering
if you could help me out.

32:21.006 --> 32:22.706
- [shaky breathing]

32:42.327 --> 32:43.693
have they put this on anyone
yet?

32:43.728 --> 32:46.229
- No one's talked about that.

32:46.264 --> 32:47.965
- I--

32:49.734 --> 32:52.669
I'm asking.

32:52.704 --> 32:55.739
Are they calling it
a command error?

32:55.774 --> 33:01.177
- It'll take time
to investigate, but, um...

33:01.212 --> 33:04.414
It looks like one.

33:04.449 --> 33:07.417
- Man, I have something
to tell you.

33:07.452 --> 33:09.719
- I know what you're gonna say.

33:09.754 --> 33:12.288
- I screwed up.
- Naturally, you'd feel that way

33:12.323 --> 33:15.492
but that's not how it went.

33:15.527 --> 33:17.227
- Casey.

33:18.430 --> 33:20.530
- You ran head-first into danger

33:20.565 --> 33:22.298
and dragged doyle to safety.

33:22.333 --> 33:25.201
Farage owes his life
to the risks you took.

33:25.236 --> 33:27.270
- You're not understanding me.
This isn't survivor's guilt

33:27.305 --> 33:30.040
or second-guessing.

33:30.075 --> 33:33.010
I deliberately broke protocol.

33:35.080 --> 33:38.382
I wasn't watching the readings.

33:39.551 --> 33:41.618
It's my fault that they're dead.

33:46.357 --> 33:49.326
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

34:05.476 --> 34:05.742
.

34:05.876 --> 34:08.078
- Casey.
- Thanks for coming, chief.

34:08.113 --> 34:09.579
- Yep. What's going on?

34:09.614 --> 34:12.248
- Not sure. Kannell said
he dropped the meter

34:12.283 --> 34:14.184
so he could be
a part of the action.

34:14.219 --> 34:16.719
- Okay.
- The guy's no glory hog.

34:16.754 --> 34:20.690
He's sharp, focused,
as steady-handed as I've seen.

34:20.725 --> 34:23.793
- Nevertheless, he made
a statement this morning.

34:23.828 --> 34:26.396
He claimed full responsibility
for the explosion.

34:26.431 --> 34:28.231
- [sighs]

34:30.235 --> 34:33.236
any chance you could walk me
through it?

34:33.271 --> 34:36.739
- Statement says he was just at
the entrance, taking readings.

34:36.774 --> 34:38.641
Doyle and the others,
they were down below

34:38.676 --> 34:40.210
clearing rubble
from the collapse.

34:40.245 --> 34:42.846
They found their victim
pinned in by rebar.

34:42.881 --> 34:45.748
They sent coleman back to
the rig to go grab some cutters.

34:45.783 --> 34:47.650
- But kannell
got the message first?

34:47.685 --> 34:51.154
- Says he set down the meter,
ran back to the rig.

34:51.189 --> 34:55.392
Just made it back down below,
and the gas ignited.

34:57.228 --> 34:59.362
- The rig was parked
right there.

34:59.397 --> 35:02.665
I'm thinking, what, 50 feet?

35:02.700 --> 35:04.701
- Give or take.

35:04.736 --> 35:08.205
- And the gas levels rose
that fast?

35:09.774 --> 35:11.408
Does that seem right to you?

35:16.681 --> 35:19.883
- No. Not at all.

35:27.492 --> 35:29.326
- Is she here?

35:30.695 --> 35:34.330
- Kelly?
- Come on in.

35:34.365 --> 35:36.166
Good to see you.

35:38.369 --> 35:40.337
- [sighs]

35:43.541 --> 35:48.145
- I--I came to make a delivery.

35:50.848 --> 35:53.216
This is from becca reed.

35:53.251 --> 35:54.817
She's a cute kid.

35:54.852 --> 35:58.254
Misses the stories
that you used to read her.

35:58.289 --> 36:00.190
- [cries softly]

36:00.225 --> 36:01.724
- I didn't tell her
what's going on.

36:01.759 --> 36:03.960
Just that you weren't
feeling good,

36:03.995 --> 36:05.862
and there was no other place
that you'd rather be

36:05.897 --> 36:07.530
than reading her a story.

36:07.565 --> 36:12.502
And she said
to give that to you,

36:12.537 --> 36:17.740
and wishes that she could
help you feel

36:17.775 --> 36:19.909
half as good
as you made her feel.

36:19.944 --> 36:23.180
- [crying softly]

36:27.485 --> 36:31.921
- just want you to know,
whether you like it or not,

36:31.956 --> 36:33.856
you're loved.

36:33.891 --> 36:35.792
You're not alone.

36:37.528 --> 36:39.996
- Kelly,

36:40.031 --> 36:41.798
I'm scared.

36:41.833 --> 36:44.400
- It's okay.
- I'm sc--I'm really--

36:44.435 --> 36:47.003
I'm scared.

36:47.038 --> 36:48.939
- It's okay.

36:52.477 --> 36:56.379
- [crying] I'm scared.
- Me too.

37:03.054 --> 37:06.289
[indistinct chatter]

37:07.959 --> 37:11.427
- hey. So, I just signed up
on Thursday for a morning shift,

37:11.462 --> 37:12.895
help the colemans
do some yard work.

37:12.930 --> 37:14.564
- Yeah. I took Wednesday.

37:16.934 --> 37:19.502
- By the way, that tea--

37:19.537 --> 37:22.272
that awful-tasting tea--

37:22.307 --> 37:24.040
it helped.

37:24.075 --> 37:26.342
Thank you.

37:26.377 --> 37:27.477
- [laughs]

37:27.512 --> 37:29.946
- well, easy come, easy go.

37:29.981 --> 37:32.448
- Aw, so sweet.

37:32.483 --> 37:34.784
- May I have your attention
for a minute?

37:34.819 --> 37:37.053
- I just got back
from chicago med.

37:37.088 --> 37:39.355
They're saying that sam farage

37:39.390 --> 37:40.990
has come through
a successful surgery.

37:41.025 --> 37:43.459
He's got a long road ahead,
but he is expected

37:43.494 --> 37:44.994
to make a full recovery.

37:45.029 --> 37:46.829
So I want to thank you all
for coming out.

37:46.864 --> 37:48.898
Um...

37:50.868 --> 37:54.537
Family, community,

37:54.572 --> 37:56.572
solidarity--

37:56.607 --> 37:58.374
those are the things
that sustain us

37:58.409 --> 38:00.376
through the hard times.

38:00.411 --> 38:04.547
They are also the things that
make this department strong.

38:04.582 --> 38:08.051
Raise your glasses.

38:08.086 --> 38:11.421
To those that have fallen,

38:11.456 --> 38:15.558
and to those
that carry their legacy.

38:15.593 --> 38:16.826
Cheers.

38:16.861 --> 38:19.329
[many, quietly] cheers.

38:19.364 --> 38:25.669
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:28.473 --> 38:31.407
- here we go again.

38:31.442 --> 38:34.444
Thanks for being with me.

38:34.479 --> 38:37.547
Just promise me that you're
gonna keep your eyes open,

38:37.582 --> 38:41.117
because my odds are not good.

38:41.152 --> 38:43.353
- Hey.

38:45.990 --> 38:49.025
I'm not thinking about odds.

38:49.060 --> 38:52.028
I'm sticking with what I know.

38:52.063 --> 38:55.932
And right now, I know
that I'm here, and so are you.

38:55.967 --> 38:58.067
- Mm-hmm.

38:58.102 --> 39:00.337
- And that's enough.

39:15.987 --> 39:17.687
[knocking at door]

39:19.624 --> 39:22.392
- hey. All right if I come in?

39:28.065 --> 39:29.465
- Beer?

39:29.500 --> 39:31.101
- I'm okay.

39:32.637 --> 39:35.104
You talk to anyone today?

39:35.139 --> 39:37.374
The other families?

39:39.110 --> 39:40.676
- No.

39:44.749 --> 39:48.651
- Sam farage had surgery today.

39:48.686 --> 39:52.555
He pulled through.
He's in recovery.

39:52.590 --> 39:56.058
He's awake, with his wife,

39:56.093 --> 39:58.094
breathing on his own.

39:59.730 --> 40:01.698
- [sighs]

40:02.700 --> 40:04.701
wasn't expecting that.

40:08.506 --> 40:11.474
Sam and aya--

40:11.509 --> 40:14.611
if they need anything--

40:16.481 --> 40:19.182
they never have to know
it came from me.

40:19.217 --> 40:21.451
- I hear you, jason.

40:24.121 --> 40:27.623
[sighs] listen.

40:27.658 --> 40:29.692
I have to ask you something.

40:32.597 --> 40:35.798
50 feet, right?

40:35.833 --> 40:39.101
From the rig to where you were
standing with the meter?

40:39.136 --> 40:42.038
- I think. Give or take.

40:42.073 --> 40:44.808
- Jason, that's impossible.

40:48.112 --> 40:51.113
As soon as we got on the scene,
we were monitoring lel levels.

40:51.148 --> 40:53.716
They were growing fast,

40:53.751 --> 40:55.785
but no way they could've gone
from safe to saturated

40:55.820 --> 40:59.789
in the time it took you
to run and grab that tool.

40:59.824 --> 41:04.160
This isn't a review board, okay?
This is you and me.

41:04.195 --> 41:07.130
What the hell happened?

41:09.300 --> 41:10.800
[sighs]

41:10.835 --> 41:13.102
you know what I think?

41:13.137 --> 41:17.640
I think doyle knew the lel
levels when you went in.

41:17.675 --> 41:23.513
I think he took a risk.
I think that risk went bad.

41:23.548 --> 41:26.182
And now you're taking the blame
to protect his memory.

41:26.217 --> 41:27.283
Am I right?

41:27.318 --> 41:29.585
- Matt.

41:29.620 --> 41:30.686
I'm asking you--

41:30.721 --> 41:33.089
- don't do this, jason.

41:33.124 --> 41:35.758
You don't tell the truth
about what happened,

41:35.793 --> 41:37.293
you'll never ride a rig again.

41:37.328 --> 41:38.761
- Let it rest.
- Absolutely not.

41:38.796 --> 41:40.029
I'm not just gonna--

41:40.064 --> 41:42.665
[pounds table]

41:42.700 --> 41:45.268
I said,

41:45.303 --> 41:47.270
let it rest.

41:47.305 --> 41:50.273
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

41:50.308 --> 41:57.547
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:09.927 --> 42:10.193
.

42:10.360 --> 42:13.095
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

42:13.130 --> 42:20.169
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
